---
title: Cheesy Mushroom Polenta with a side o’ Garlic Bread
description: Few things are more comforting than a bowl of polenta. Not familiar with the Italian dish? Basically, it’s a creamy, cheesy cornmeal porridge that acts as the perfect bed for all kinds of delicious toppings. Ours is as unfussy as it is delicious. It cooks to perfection in a mere 10 minutes, no constant stirring required! (Sorry, you’ll have to get your weekly arm workout elsewhere!) Ladled on top, there’s an ultra-savory ragu made with meaty mushrooms, juicy tomatoes, and aromatic garlic and scallions. It’s luxurious and deliciously simple at the same time. Oh, and did we mention there’s also a side of garlic ciabatta? Buon appetito!
